<div align='center'><font size='4'><b>BUNDLE UP WITH STYLE: WINTER FASHION APPROACHES</b></font><br>
<img src='http://graphics.millsberry.com/site_gfx/interiors/gazette/gazette_20071101.jpg' border='1'>
</div>
<br>
<b>Thursday, November  1, 2007</b> &mdash; As those cold north winds begin to blow in, the citizens of Millsberry are wondering what to wear. <br><br>Once again, it&#039;s time to break out your winter garments and layer up. Many are faced with the familiar problem that presents itself this time of year: How do I remain stylish in all of my bulky winter clothes? <br><br>Does fashion hibernate during the winter months? Are you forced to sacrifice personal style for the sake of warmth and comfort? <br><br>Some would argue yes, but, in fact, it&#039;s quite the opposite. The more articles of clothing you wear, the more chances you&#039;ll have to add to the particular look and style you&#039;re cultivating. The odds of looking fabulous are really in your favor as winter approaches.<br><br><br>
<br>
We enlisted the help of Loretta Rivers, resident fashion guru and owner of the <br><a href=http://www.millsberry.com/shop.phtml?shop_id=1>Clothing Store</a>, for some tips on how to keep it classy during those bitter winter months.<br><br>&quot;The first thing you want to keep in mind about winter fashion is that layers are key. Not only do they keep you warm, but they&#039;re also an opportunity to mix and match different styles&quot;, said Loretta, as she thumbed through a rack of winter clothes.<br><br>&quot;Sometimes it&#039;s good to even wear more than one coat. Leather is really in right now. It also happens to be very warm as well, so that&#039;s an added bonus. The other great thing about winter is it gives you opportunities to combine all sorts of accessories.&quot;<br><br>Loretta then moves to a table presenting an assortment of scarves hats and vests. <br><br>&quot;Scarves are another way to really give your outfit that extra flare that&#039;s missing. Of course, with any scarf, you have to find the way to wear it that best suits you and your personal style. There are many different ways to tie a scarf, so that just adds to the different combinations you can create. Scarves are also really great when you can match them with a hat. You either want to pick a hat that&#039;s the same color, or a complimentary color to your scarf.&quot;<br><br>Loretta quickly turns and sashays over to the Winter Tops Collection.<br><br>&quot;Five years ago, Turtlenecks were out, but now they&#039;re in. They&#039;re the new sweater vest, and now sweater vests are out. That&#039;s fashion for you though. It&#039;s always changing. I love it. Now, lets not forget footwear. Footwear can make or break an outfit.&quot;<br><br>As she says this, she scurries over to the shoe department.<br><br>&quot;You have to make sure you have a solid pair of boots for winter. Something that looks great, but also something that you&#039;re going to be able to wear in the snow and bad weather.&quot;<br><br>Thanks to Loretta, feeling warm and looking great during winter are back in style.<br><br></div>
